Text.Value: Agreed - let's finish this.
What are you going to do?
Not yet.
Increased heartbeat, audible tremble - you're lying.

EditorData.NodeContext: cocks head to one side with a feeling of dread

Text.Value: I cannot follow you - not with what lies ahead. End it, and I shall join you.

EditorData.NodeContext: clearly very disturbed and kinda freaked out

Text.Value: Some hostages died, but your daughter wasn't one of them.
I will bring down not only the Steel Watch - but the very Foundry itself. This place will be smoke and rubble when I am finished. Are you ready, my friend?
This is hardly the time for errands. Do as you wish, but then we must go.
Blessed Gond, where did you - never mind. I will go to my grave happier not knowing.
My fellow Gondians! Flee this prison. We're bringing this place down.
You monster!
Not yet.
We need to move - the Neurocitor lies in the depths of the Foundry.
Do it.
It is time - let us bring down the Foundry, and the Steel Watch with it.
Gond - let your hammer be my courage, your furnace my heart.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: begins typing (shot form behind) - we see a shot of something spark.

Text.Value: I put my trust, my faith, in you - for nothing?
Short, annoying, doesn't shut up about Gond? Yeah, she survived.
The Neurocitor. I can hear its hum - familiar, yet painful.
Let's go.
Our destination is the Neurocitor - the nerve centre of the Steel Watch. Guide me there, and I'll do the rest.
Your bomb will most certainly do the trick. Place it directly on the Neurocitor - and then run like every fiend of the Nine Hells snaps at your heels.
I don't need you. I have a runepowder bomb. Won't that do the trick?
I helped design the Steel Watchers, toiled night and day on the first bipedal prototype. It is fitting it ends this way.
The prison exploded, but I got everyone out.
I'll deal with them - when the time is right.
Our destination is the Neurocitor - the nerve centre of the Steel Watch. Guide me there, and I'll do the rest.
What happened to Obelia? Is she safe?

EditorData.NodeContext: panicked (trying and failing to be calm)

Text.Value: We're bringing this place down.
My heart - I thought her lost. I would give more than just my sight to keep her safe.
Be swift - we've been lucky so far. I don't wish to push Gond's favour any further.
Blow this place to the Nine Hells, my friend - end this nightmare.
Did you see what happened? Is my little girl - is Obelia safe?
We are losing time. You must guide me to the Neurocitor, before the Banites send reinforcements.
Lead the way - I'll listen to your steps and bring up the rear.
I'm sorry - she didn't make it.
Like the Foundry, the Neurocitor's exterior is near impossible to penetrate. However, its inner circuitry is highly unstable. I'm going to rain fire upon it - from the inside out.
You did the impossible, so it is only fair I return the favour. The Steel Watch must be destroyed - and I will help you do it.
She's safe and sound.
This was all a ploy, wasn't it? To fool us into having hope? I can't believe I trusted you -monster.
You mean you were there, yet you did nothing?!
She is - don't worry.

Synopsis:
A talk with Toobin, Gondian leader after the Iron Throne.
He asks the player to go to the lowest floor of the Foundry and destroy the Control Centre.
